Sentencas: In this work, a tubular ceramic-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) was successfully fabricated by a low cost and simple process involving phase-inversion, brush coating and co-sintering.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: Properties including sintering behavior, microstructure of the tubular support as well as the electrochemical properties of single cell were investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: The results show that a porous tubular support with finger- like pores and macrovoids was obtained after phase-inversion process.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: The tubular support is proved to be gas-permeable after sintering at 1400 degrees C with shrinkage of about 34%.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: The maximum power density of single tubular SOFC is 100 mW/cm(2) and 122 mW/cm(2) at 850 degrees C when fed with wet methane and hydrogen, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: The current collection, thickness of electrolyte and gas permeability of tubular support should account for the large total resistance.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method

Sentencas: The present tubular design could be expected to deliver a higher voltage for longer support with several segmented-in-series cell stacks.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of Tubular SOFC Based on a Porous Ceramic Support Fabricated by Phase-Inversion Method
